The paper presents a novel approach to population-based RL in continuous control, which involves leveraging properties of normalizing flows to perform attractive and repulsive operations between current members of the population and previously observed policies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
